r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-PAXTV-MIRACLE02-COX     10-01 0501
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PAXTV-MIRACLE02-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    'Miracle' works miracles for Pax TV
 &HT;    By Marguerite M. Plunkett
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Richard Thomas, whose role as John-Boy in The WaltonsThe
Walton's was as wholesome as wholesome gets, will host family
friendly PAX TV's show ``It's a Miracle,'' Paxson Communications
Chairman Lowell ``Bud'' Paxson said recently.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas joins actress Nia Peeples as co-host of the show,
replacing country singer Billy Dean. The change is set for this
Sunday Oct. 4.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're tweaking 'It's a Miracle,''' Paxson said. ``It's like
our Mona Lisa -- we just have to change the frame.''
</P>
<P>
   Lea Sloan, spokeswoman for the West Palm Beach-based Paxson
Communications, said that Dean had been signed for only three
episodes. ``He has a very active music deal which is making it
impossible for him to do two things,'' Sloan said.
</P>
<P>
   Dean's publicist, Lisa Gladfelter Bell of Force Inc. in
Nashville, said, ``It was mutual.''
</P>
<P>
   Dean was traveling more than he had expected between Nashville
and Los Angeles, she said.
</P>
<P>
   Gladfelter Bell also said the new host was one of many changes
for the month-old series. ``They seem to be struggling with this
one,'' she said. ``I know they changed the format and got a whole
new production company. (Dean) just kind of bailed out. It was one
of those mutual things.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a Miracle'' is a one-hour weekly series that airs at 9
p.m. Sunday. The program tells stories of real-life miracles, such
as a pet that saved family members' lives and the success of a
young man who started life as a drug-addicted, abandoned baby.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's one of the shows that's getting an incredible reaction,''
Paxson said. The program invites viewers to tell of their miracles,
Paxson said, noting that the show has now collected enough tales to
last it into the millennium.
</P>
<P>
   ``People don't realize how often God shows his face in people's
lives,'' Paxson said.
</P>
<P>
   It's a Miracle is one of the original shows the nation's new
seventh network is airing. PAX's foundation is reruns of Touched by
an Angel, Diagnosis Murder and Dr. Quinn, Medicine Woman. But it
also airs original programming, including new episodes of Flipper
and Neon Rider .
</P>
<P>
   Thomas already stars in a program that runs Sunday mornings on
PAX: The Adventures of Swiss Family Robinson. The show runs as part
of the block of children's programming on Saturday and Sunday
mornings that PAX has dubbed Cloud Nine.
</P>
<P>
   While Gladfelter Bell said Dean doesn't have any other
television shows lined up yet, he is starring in a movie of the
week, Makeover, Paxson Communications (AMEX: PAX, $9.19) launched
PAX Aug. 31. The network programming will air on 95 stations that
Paxson will own, operate or is affiliated with once all its deals
are completed. The stations are in markets with more than 76
million households with televisions.
</P>
<P>
   Paxson's West Palm Beach station is WPXP-Channel 67.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
