<P>
   PIGEONS-PBP _ Jaunty crime tales are at least as old as the 18th
century and The Beggar's Opera. But they were never standard fare.
Late this century, however, a dark comedy about your average serial
killer is as common as bloody murder itself. Wild and crazy
mischief pays. Examples are Elmore Leonard's novels and the Coen
brothers' movies. (Schwan, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PIGEONS-VAUGHN _ Elvis Eyes. Vince Vaughn's got them. But wait.
He didn't have them in The Lost World: Jurassic Park. Or did he?
Maybe he wore them for his of a wannabe Lothario in Swingers _ the
breakthrough movie for the 28-year-old actor? (Schwan, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
