   TEENS-TALK _ Teens who talk with their mother about sex are much
less likely to experiment and much more likely to use a condom when
they do, CDC researchers say in a report in the American Journal of
Public Health. (Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
