</P>
<P>
   PEDESTRIAN-FATALITIES _ ATLANTA _ A two-day national conference
in Atlanta on preventing childhood pedestrian fatalities discussed
``traffic calming'' features _ such as speed humps, curb extentions
and refuge islands. But the most obvious pedestrian aid, which is
only now debuting in some suburban Atlanta neighborhoods, and is
still nonexistent in many others, is the sidewalk. ''We need
policies that say the sidewalk goes in as soon as the street gets
built,'' said Dan Burden, a Florida based pedestrian advocate and
traffic engineer. (Ledford, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
