<P>
   TITANIC-BACKSTATGE (New York) _ Audiences generally know a
production by its stars, story, music. Rarely do they get a glimpse
behind the scenes, where the set and costume changes can be as
intricately choreographed as the dancing, where the relationships
may be easily as intense as those the actors portray on stage, and
where the unexpected crises can be even more suspenseful than the
plot. ``Titanic'' offers a particularly compelling example of the
magnitude and the minutiae of this backstage drama. By Robin
Pogrebin.
</P>
