structure is pretty simple. A fund of hedge funds takes your money
and divides it among anywhere from six to 80 hedge fund managers _
like Long-Term Capital. The goal is to put your money in the hands
of savvy managers who do not limit themselves to investments as
mundane as stocks and to spread the risk. By Geraldine Fabrikant.
