<P>
   PLANE_ The newest Lockheed C-130 Hercules pays a visit to
Wright-Patterson AFB, which manages the acquistion of new
airplanes. This is part of a ``world tour'' Lockheed is giving to
its latest Hercules makeover. The Air Force just awarded a contract
to modify six C-130Js into ``hurricane hunter'' weather
reconnaissance planes. The contract includes an option for four
more, with a total potential value of almost $60 million. Lockheed
builds the C-130 at its plant in Marietta, Ga. (Gaffney, Dayton
Daily News) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   NAVISTAR-STRIKE _ SPRINGFIELD, Ohio _ Two unions representing
150 Navistar workers settle dispute with company and remain on the
job. (Springfield News-Sun) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   COXCOMMUNICATIONS _ ATLANTA _ Cox Communications is expected
today to close its purchase of the Las Vegas cable system, one of
the largest single systems in the country. (Haddad, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   FOREX _ AUSTIN _ A state district judge recently froze assets
that Russell Erxleben may have received from his failed Austin
Forex International Inc. The move prevents him from moving money
from investors into other accounts or from selling items such as
autos that are owned by the company. It lasts until a civil trial
on charges against Erxleben and several other defendants is held. A
preliminary trial date was set for May. (Tyson, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
