Faso. (Melvin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CARTER-ASIA _ Carter Center plans South Asia program. (Graham,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HIMALAYA-INDICTMENT _ AUSTIN, Texas _ It's a harrowing case. A
15-year-old girl is thrown off a carnival ride and killed as her
father watches. But is it murder? The murder indictments shocked
legal observers, who said it is unusual for any criminal charges to
be filed against company executives in such cases, much less murder
charges. (Banta/Quin, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-GANGS _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Warning that Texas faces a growing
threat from organized crime gangs, a special Texas Senate committee
is poised to recommend creation of a statewide Violent Gang Task
Force to better coordinate gang enforcement and monitoring efforts.
(Ward, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CHRISTIAN-FUNDING _ Should universities be allowed to provide
operating money to student organizations geared toward a single
racial or sexual orientation while denying Christian student
organizations or political groups similar funding? The question
lies at the heart of a federal lawsuit filed recently in U.S.
District Court in Cincinnati. (Fisher, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
