<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AIKMAN NOT DEFINITE FOR NEXT GAME
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
By KEVIN LYONS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Although Troy Aikman continues to insist he will
return for the Oct. 11 game against the Carolina Panthers, coach
Chan Gailey is not so sure.
</P>
<P>
   ``It would take a miracle for him to be ready by Carolina _ it'd
be amazing,'' Gailey said after practice yesterday. ``Maybe he can
be the third (quarterback) and hand off if we got in a bind late.
But as I see it right now, it'd be tough.''
</P>
<P>
   Gailey has watched Aikman throw to wide receivers in practice
this week, but Gailey has not talked to him. Aikman, who fractured
his left collarbone in the first half of a Sept. 13 game against
the Denver Broncos, was expected to miss four to eight weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman could not be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Since his rehab began, Aikman has circled the Panthers game as
his return date. He began throwing for the first time last week.
And he is expected to get an X-ray on his collarbone Monday to see
how he is progressing.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want him to think he can come back early,'' Gailey said, ``I
want him to try to make it if he can. If so, that'd be great.''
</P>
<P>
   Aikman has said that he does not expect his bone to be healed
completely if he comes back earlier than team trainer Jim Maurer
expects. Gailey said Aikman would probably have to practice the
entire week to show he has no limitations before Gailey would
insert him into the starting lineup.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everyone is optimistic,'' Maurer said. ``We just have to wait
and see. When you say four to eight weeks, it could mean four weeks
or it could mean eight.''
</P>
<P>
   If Aikman can't play against the Panthers, the Cowboys' next
game is at Chicago on Oct. 18. With a bye week coming up Oct. 25,
Gailey could hold Aikman out until the club's Nov. 2 game at
Philadelphia. That would give Aikman seven weeks from the time of
the injury to heal.
</P>
<P>
   ``But there is also a temptation to play'' Aikman, Gailey said.
``There are a lot of things to consider, and we will take it all
under consideration when the time comes.'' &QL; 
BRIEFLY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Deion Sanders fell awkwardly and sprained his left ankle in
practice. The Cowboys listed him as probable on the NFL injury
report.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Irvin is not on the injury report, but he has had some
soreness in his right ankle and did not participate in some
portions of practice yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Emmitt Smith (groin), Leon Lett (knee) and Daryl Johnston
(swelling in knee) returned to practice yesterday after missing
Wednesday's workout.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
